---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="DoItSwift Pro"
  description="Future Pro tier for power users: advanced workflows and extras. Core DoItSwift tools stay free in your browser."
  keywords="doitswift pro, online tools pro"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>DoItSwift Pro</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Today, every DoItSwift tool is free and runs in your browser — no account required. We are planning an optional
        <strong>Pro</strong> tier for people who want more: faster batch flows, saved presets, priority support, and
        other power-user features.
      </p>

      <h2>What stays free</h2>
      <p>
        Core conversion, compression, resizing, and encoding features you use today are intended to remain available
        without a subscription. Pro is about going further for those who need it — not locking basics behind a paywall.
      </p>

      <h2>What Pro might include</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Advanced batch and automation options</li>
        <li>Preset packs and reusable settings</li>
        <li>Priority support and early access to new tools</li>
        <li>Additional export and workflow integrations over time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Details and pricing will be announced when we are ready. Nothing changes for casual users who are happy with the
        free tools.
      </p>

      <h2>Have input?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have a feature you would pay for — or something you never want paywalled — tell us on the{' '}
        <a href="/contact" class="link-back">contact page</a>. It genuinely shapes what we build next.
      </p>

      <p><a href="/" class="link-back">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
